<div class="lang-en">
<section id="what-is-bazi">
      <h2>What Is BaZi?</h2>

      <div class="image-panel">
        <img src="/img/photos/ink-painting-mountains.webp" alt="Chinese ink painting of mountain landscape — scholarly tradition" loading="lazy">
        <div class="image-panel-caption">
          <h3>The Art of Eight Characters</h3>
          <p>Mapping cosmic energies at the moment of birth</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>BaZi (<span class="chinese-char">八字</span>, literally "eight characters") constructs a destiny chart from four pillars derived from the year, month, day, and hour of birth. Each pillar consists of a Heavenly Stem and Earthly Branch, yielding eight characters that encode the <a href="/wuxing/">Five Elements</a>, Yin-Yang polarity, and seasonal energy.</p>

      <div class="stat-highlight">
        <span class="stat-highlight-number">8</span>
        <div class="stat-highlight-text"><strong>Characters</strong> from 4 Pillars form the foundation of every BaZi chart — a nuanced analytical framework closer to personality typology than fortune-telling.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="historical-origins">
      <h2>Historical Origins</h2>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-date">Tang Dynasty (618-907 CE)</div>
          <h3>Li Xuzhong (<span class="chinese-char">李虛中</span>)</h3>
          <p>Developed the Three Pillars method using year, month, and day of birth. Demonstrated that Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches encoded meaningful destiny patterns.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-date">Song Dynasty (960-1279 CE)</div>
          <h3>Xu Ziping (<span class="chinese-char">徐子平</span>) — The Revolution</h3>
          <p>Added the hour pillar and established the Day Master as the central reference point. Created the <em>Ziping method</em> (<span class="chinese-char">子平法</span>) — the orthodox classical approach still used today.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-date">Key Texts</div>
          <h3>Classical Canon</h3>
          <p><em>Yuanhai Ziping</em> (<span class="chinese-char">淵海子平</span>, Song), <em>Sanming Tonghui</em> (<span class="chinese-char">三命通會</span>, Ming), <em>Zi Ping Zhen Quan</em> (<span class="chinese-char">子平真詮</span>) — the most rigorous pre-Qing texts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

